---
import Card from "../unitComponents/Card.astro";
---

<section class="w-full mt-10 md:mt-20 flex flex-col gap-10 font-bold">
    <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-[10%] px-8 md:px-32 text-grisT font-bold">
        <Card>
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Precision Temperature Control:</h2>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin">
                Maintains exact temperatures with a tolerance of ±1°C, ensuring optimal conditions for material processing.
            </p>
        </Card>
        <Card>
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Customizable Heating Capacity: </h2>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin">
                Tailored to meet specific project needs, from small-scale operations to large industrial requirements.
            </p>
        </Card>
        <Card>
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">High-Efficiency Burners:</h2>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin">
                Equipped with low-NOx burners that reduce emissions while maximizing fuel efficiency.
            </p>
        </Card>
        <Card>
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl">Thermal Oil Circulation System: 
            </h2>
            <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin">
                Ensures even heat distribution across the entire system, preventing hot spots and material degradation.
            </p>
        </Card>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center w-full">
        <h2 class="text-blueMain text-xl md:text-2xl">
            Stand out from the competition by offering the highest-quality mix.
        </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full px-8 md:px-32">
        <Card>
            <h2 class="text-blueMain text-xl md:text-2xl">
                Oil Heater option available instead of direct-fire heating system in asphalt storage tanks.
            </h2><br>
            <ul class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg list-disc ml-6">
                <li>With heating capacities of 1,000,000 and 2,400,000 Btu/Hr.</li>
                <li>Includes a high-efficiency 2” diameter coil system inside the asphalt tank.</li>
                <li>Connections for asphalt tankers with coil heating systems.</li>
                <li>Thermally insulated with ceramic fiber.</li>
                <li>Stainless steel exterior sheet covering.</li>
                <li>Equipped with a diesel burner.</li>
                <li>Automatic on/off control based on temperature.</li>
                <li>Two operating modes: Automatic and Manual.</li>
                <li>Digital thermometers with programmable set point for burner activation and shutoff.</li>
                <li>Siemens PLC-based control system.</li>
                <li>100-liter (26.4-gallon) thermal oil expansion tank.</li>
                <li>100% duty cycle.</li>
                <li>Includes safety systems and automatic shutdown in case of errors.</li>
            </ul>
        </Card>

    </div>
    <div class="w-full px-8 md:px-32">
        <div class="w-full">
            <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-blueMain">Different Applications</h2><br>
            <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-grisT">
                Triaso oil heaters are designed and manufactured in-house for our own projects,
                 but they are also suitable for a wide range of applications.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
    <div class="w-full px-8 md:px-32 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-[7%]">
        <div class="w-full font-bold">
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl text-center">Expansion Tank</h2><br>
            <p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg">
                Our oil heater ensures uniform heat distribution through advanced thermal oil circulation. It features a built-in expansion 
                tank that absorbs oil volume changes due to temperature, stabilizing pressure and protecting the system for longer, 
                maintenance-free operation.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full font-bold">
            <h2 class="text-lg md:text-xl text-center">High-Performance Recirculation Pump: </h2><br>
            <p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg">
                Equipped with a high-performance recirculation pump designed to maintain a constant flow of thermal oil,
                 ensuring efficient heat transfer. Available with a 10 HP or 15 HP motor depending on system capacity, it supports continuous
                  operation with low maintenance and optimal energy use.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-white w-full px-8 md:px-32 font-bold py-6">
        <div class="">
            <h1 class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-grisT">Oil Coil</h1><br>
            <p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg">
                Inside the thermal oil heater, the coil—or heat exchanger—is where the thermal oil flows through a tightly wound spiral 
                of steel tubing. This coil is heated indirectly by the burner, transferring heat to the oil without combustion gases mixing with it.
                 Once the oil reaches the desired temperature, it circulates through the system to heat the target application, such as an asphalt 
                 tank or other industrial equipment, delivering consistent and efficient thermal energy
            </p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <img src="" alt="">
        </div>
    </div>
</section>